= **Introduction** =

----

With all the available tools and possibilities which come with ROS. MATLAB/SIMULINK gives us an additional range of solutions for testing and implementing new ROS nodes in our ROS environment. Also the handling of ROS Nodes with MATLAB/SIMULINK is a little less abstract.

What we will do in this Tutorial to get a good idea of how ROS Works with Matlab and Simulink.
And how to let your ROS-nodes communicate with each other when they are located on different platforms.

To perform this Tutorial the official "Robotics System Toolbox" from MATLAB/SIMULINK needs to be installed.
It's recommended to work through [[Main.Projekte.MoRoP.ROS GettingStarted]] previous to this Tutorial.


